Name: chronic lymphocytic leukemia
Definition: A lymphoblastic leukemia characterized by over production of B-cells and their accumulation in bone marrow and blood.

Name: precursor lymphoblastic lymphoma leukemia
Definition: A lymphoblastic leukemia that has_material_basis_in immature malignant lymphocytes (lymphoblasts) committed to the B-cell or T-cell lineage and located in bone marrow and located in peripheral blood.

Name: obsolete T-cell neoplasm
Definition: A lymphoblastic leukemia that has_material_basis_in immature malignant lymphocytes (lymphoblasts) committed to the B-cell or T-cell lineage and located in bone marrow and located in peripheral blood.

Name: plasmacytic leukemia
Definition: A sinusitis which involves infection of ethmoid sinuses that causes pain or pressure behind and between the eyes

Name: obsolete multiple myeloma and immunoproliferative neoplasm
Definition: A sinusitis which involves infection of ethmoid sinuses that causes pain or pressure behind and between the eyes

Name: obsolete abortion complicated by renal failure
Definition: A sinusitis which involves infection of ethmoid sinuses that causes pain or pressure behind and between the eyes

Name: acute lymphocytic leukemia
Definition: A lymphoblastic leukemia that is characterized by over production of lymphoblasts.
